import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby(['year'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data_grouped['year'], data_grouped['rate'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title('What is the trend of unemployment rate across all industries from 2000 to 2010?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_2010 = data[data['year'] == 2010]
    industry_unemployment = data_2010.groupby('series')['rate'].mean()
    max_unemployment = industry_unemployment.max()

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    industry_unemployment.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.axhline(y=max_unemployment, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_unemployment:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in 2010?')
    plt.xlabel('Industry')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_2005 = data[data['year'] == 2005]
    
    plt.hist(data_2005['rate'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    
    median_rate = data_2005['rate'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_rate, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {median_rate:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rate across all industries in 2005?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_2008 = data[data['year'] == 2008]
    industry_counts = data_2008.groupby('series')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    industry_counts = industry_counts.sort_values('count', ascending=False)

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.bar(industry_counts['series'], industry_counts['count'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.axhline(industry_counts['count'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {industry_counts['count'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("Which industry had the highest number of unemployed people in 2008?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
